 the guild decided)
\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Buy small potions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Use remaining gold on main stat and constitution (before you unlock gems,
 try to have slightly more main stat than const).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Wait until all 50 players have 4/6 skills and the guild has 40% GOLD and
 60% XP bonuses (or 50% / 50%).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Don't do any arena fights yet, save them for later.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Do quests only until you reach level 10.
\series default

\begin_inset Newline linebreak
\end_inset


\series bold
Only choose XP quests!
\series default
 Calculate which quests give the most XP per minute of thirst.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
If you are a druid, equip the bear mask.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
At level 10
\series default
 stop doing quests, refresh Magic Shop, and 
\series bold
buy Scrapbook
\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Equip your character with all items (except Talisman, you can't buy it from
 the shop before level 15).
 At level 10 you can find items with +20 stats (total main+constitution),
 but you need to refresh the shops much more to find those.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Spend remaining gold on stats.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Login from another device to get the +5 stats for the achievement.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Start attacking players in the Hall of fame in order to fill the album.
 Choose players with different levels and classes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Your goal 
\series bold
at level 10 is to fill about 25% of album
\series default
 before touching quests.
 If you want to have more than that, you need to raise your stats enough,
 so that you are able to defeat higher level players.
 That might be expensive, so you can stop around 25% (550 stickers) and
 continue improving album to +40% at level 15 (when you equip better potions).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Don't forget to spend all gold for stats after each attack.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Do a few quests
\series default
 (hopefully 2-3 only), until you find the 
\series bold
key for the first dungeon
\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Since you raised your stats with gold while you were filling the album,
 you might be able to kill the first 3-4 monsters.
 In general the idea is to always 
\series bold
try dungeons before doing more quests
\series default
.
 Clearing a few floors of a dungeon gives you enough XP to level up, which
 means you will later play quests at a higher level, receiving more XP from
 your thirst.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
If you have a PC and lots of free time, you can save some mushrooms by using
 the Dungeon Simulator from sftools to check the chances for winning a dungeon,
 before actually trying it (https://sftools.mar21.eu/dungeons.html, thank mar21
 from the Tavern Discord for creating this!).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Once blocked at the dungeon, try improving album again.
 You should be higher level now, and can defeat more players with stickers
 you need.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Wait until about 1-2 hours before server reset time
\series default
 (communicate that with your guild first, as some people find that selfish),
 so that more players have increased their guild skills, and there are also
 more stickers available on the server.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Do quests to reach level 15
\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Refresh the Magic Shop to 
\series bold
buy a Talisman and medium potions
\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Refresh the Weapon Shop and 
\series bold
buy a new weapon
\series default
 (of course also check if other items offered are better).
 You will change all items at level 18 again.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate

\series bold
Clear 1-2 more dungeon floors.

\series default
 When you reach the Banshee monster (with level 22) you can stop, as it
 is hard to defeat at level 15 for most classes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Around level 15 it should be possible to collect enough gold to upgrade
 your Treasure skill (if you went for 4/6) or Instructor (if you went for
 5/5).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Since you changed equipment and are stronger now, you can 
\series bold
improve album again
\series default
.
 At that level, you can already collect between 30% and 40% of album, how
